		    Meridian Asset Management
		  
		


























Toggle navigation





Meridian Asset Management













Welcome
Meridian Asset Management was founded to create value for our clients by preserving and growing their assets. We do this by listening to their goals and carefully crafting bespoke investment portfolios tailored to the client's needs and the dynamics of the markets.
Investors Login Email Login













ABOUT US
Meridian Asset Management (“Meridian”) formed in 2012, is an Asset Manager and Private Merchant Banking Group led by senior professionals with over 100 years of combined experience in the securities, derivatives, insurance, private equity and hedge fund industries.





Asset Management
Meridian is the investment manager for the Meridian Global Opportunities Fund SPC (the ”Fund”), an exempted company incorporated in the Cayman Islands and registered as a segregated portfolio company. The Fund has established multiple segregated portfolios with investment objectives ranging from principal protection with yield generation to private equity.
Additionally, Meridian provides support and infrastructure services for top managers they select, and who are interested in building their own asset management business.





Private Merchant Banking Group
Meridian’s Private Merchant Banking Group sources assets for principal investment or acquisition by Meridian’s fund complex, thus creating unique investment opportunities for Meridian’s investors.
The Private Merchant Banking Group has the ability to manage assets invested in the Fund as well as syndicate and co-invest our own capital. Professionals within the group have over 50 years of management experience in multiple industries.












OUR SERVICES
Meridian provides innovative financial solutions to both our investors and corporate clients. 




Investment Management
Asset Management

Meridian invests in successful managers with experience across all major asset classes, and who have been successful in volatile markets. Meridian’s investors and syndication partners include: reinsurance companies, family offices, hedge funds, captive insurance companies, and private equity funds.
In 2014, Meridian expanded its reach and capabilities into Europe by opening several representative offices.




Merchant Banking
Private Merchant Banking Group

With extensive knowledge of both sides of the balance sheet, Meridian provides creative solutions to maximize stakeholder value for our clients who have with existing revenue and capital deployment needs. These bespoke solutions may include: senior and subordinated debt, acquisition finance, and forward sale structures.
In addition to funding solutions, Meridian’s team provides advisory, structuring and operational support services for its clients and investments.












Our Partners
Meridian is led by senior professionals with over 100 years of combined experience in the securities, derivatives, insurance, private equity and hedge fund industries. 




Asset Management & Corporate









						          John Geraci
						        




Founding Partner
Mr. Geraci has been involved in money management and private equity for more than 25 years. His first principle investment was the purchase of First Equity Group of Florida, which was the largest indigenous brokerage, investment-banking firm in the state at that time. As Chairman, he has directed the company to focus on international business and increased profits significantly in one year. After a successful exit, Geraci founded Meridian Capital Markets, a boutique private equity investor and consulting firm.
Mr. Geraci was the past Managing General Partner of Meridian Capital Partners, LP a $600 million private equity Partnership formed in 2001 that focused on targeted venture opportunities globally. Meridian Capital has invested in more than 40 private companies and various oil and gas assets throughout the United States. Mr. Geraci is a past board member and shareholder of Magister S.A., a top performing pension administrator in Chile. Prior to Meridian Capital Ventures, Mr. Geraci was the Senior Managing Director of Preferred Capital Markets, Inc., and a New York Stock Exchange Member Firm.
Mr. Geraci is a frequent guest speaker to International Private Equity forums, donates time to non-profit organizations in the community and on the Florida Bar Grievance Committee.







									Yiannis Chryssanthakopoulos
						        




Mr. Chryssanthakopoulos has 9 years of international consulting and project development experience, and was one of the pioneers of the Greek Renewable Energy Market; providing project development, finance and investment sourcing services to operators.
In 2011, Mr. Chryssanthakopoulos founded a boutique consulting firm in London, United Kingdom. The company's unique business model offered clients the combined expertise of 120 partnering firms with over 300 years of market related experience.
Prior to joining Meridian, Mr. Chryssanthakopoulos worked in multiple sectors including energy, real estate, product trading. He has also completed several M&A transactions, and provided multiple services including: capital raising, management consulting and investment advisory. The breadth of Mr. Chryssanthakopoulos’ experiences has enabled him to develop a unique network of Ultra High Net Worth (“UHNW”) clientele and global business connections.







									Oskars Gudrais
								




Oskars Gudrais has more than 14 years International experience as an investor, business manager and investment relations professional, while working in multiple organizations, including: the Latvian Italian Joint Stock Company (JSC) Unilat Corporation, Straightline International (New York), Anna McBride Company (New York), New York Private Commercial Banks, and Context Capital Group (New York).
During last 10 years, Mr. Gudrais was Chairman of The Board for Conrad Holding Group (“CHG”), one of the International Investment Companies in Latvia. CHG focuses on linking Western and Russian investors.
From 1995 till 2001, Mr. Gudrais worked for the Ministry of Economy for the Republic of Latvia. Additionally, the European Commission nominated him as a director for the EU Structural Fund. Mr. Gudrais role as director was to coordinate the pre-accession procedures for Latvia, focusing on decentralization implementation systems (DIS), and accounting and reporting procedures. During this period, Mr. Gudrais also worked for the University of Helsinki’s Knowledge Services as a business consultant and advisor, specializing in long term investment planning, company analysis and business administration.
Mr Gudrais completed a Msc in International Law at Latvian State University in Riga and is skilled in multiple languages.







						          Bill Cason
						        




General Counsel, Meridian Asset Management
Bill Cason began his career with Conoco after graduating in 1981 with a Bachelor of Science in Chemical Engineering. While at Conoco, Mr. Cason gained experience in refining, pipelines and oilfield operations, including postings to Singapore and England, culminating as Special Assistant to the Chief Executive Officer (Dino Nicandros).
In 1996 Mr. Cason graduated Law School at the University of Houston Law Center with a Doctorate of Juris Prudence, Magna Cum Laude and accepted a position with Mayor, Day, Caldwell and Keeton, LLP, as an associate attorney focused on domestic and international Oil and Gas issues.
Starting in 1998 Mr. Cason accepted the first of many Associate General Counsel or General Counsel positions, joining Ocean Energy as Associate General Counsel. From 1998, through 2010, Mr. Cason held similar positions with Devon Energy, Anadarko Petroleum and Gaither Petroleum where he operated in multiple international jurisdictions.
In 2012 Mr. Cason joined Greenfields Petroleum as their VP of Business Development, and has recently taken on the responsibility of Chief Compliance Officer for the corporation.
Mr. Cason is fluent in spoken French, and holds a Commercial Pilot’s license, IFR, Multi-Engine land.










Private Merchant Banking Group









						          Jamie Boyden
						        




Partner
Mr. Boyden has over 17 years of experience working as an investment banker in Canada and the U.S. with multiple firms. Prior to joining Meridian, Mr. Boyden was an Executive Director of Ascendant Securities, Inc. where he ran the firm’s energy investment banking business. Mr. Boyden worked at Pope & Company, where he helped build the firm’s institutional business and Energy coverage.
Additionally, Mr. Boyden has over 10 years of investment banking experience at Lehman Brothers (Toronto), UBS Securities (New York), Bear Stearns (Dallas) and Cantor Fitzgerald (Toronto), working in multiple industries: including Oil & Gas, Financial Institutions and Gaming.
Through his career, Mr. Boyden has completed over $8 bn of M&A and $2 bn of corporate finance advisory transactions.
Mr. Boyden has a Master of Arts from the University of Toronto, and Bachelor of Arts from Tufts University and is currently a CFA candidate.







									Rich MacDougal
								




Head of Energy Operations
Mr. MacDougal has a unique blend of International Business Development and Petroleum Operations experience that uniquely qualifies him to start up new operations anywhere in the world. He is a registered petroleum engineer and a leader of petroleum engineering and operations both domestically and internationally. He has a proven record in the drilling, development and exploitation of discoveries and of existing fields in the Gulf of Mexico, Alaska, Offshore California, Pakistan, Indonesia, Argentina, Tunisia, Kazakhstan and Azerbaijan. As a results-oriented team leader and member, Mr. MacDougal is able to use his strong managerial and technical skills to increase the profitability and development of an organization. Mr. MacDougal is a retired LCDR US Navy, 10 years with Exxon and 10 Years with Union Texas Petroleum
Over the last 15 years, Mr. MacDougal has held multiple senior positions including:

President and Founder, Viridis Petroleum SEZC
COO and Founder, Greenfields Petroleum LLC
President, COO and Founder, GFI Oil & Gas Inc.
Vice President of International Projects, Anadarko Petroleum Corporation
Vice President, Acquisitions & Joint Ventures, Hurricane Hydrocarbons
Sr. Vice President, First International Oil








									Jonathan Pirie
						        




Director of Diligence and Forensic Accounting
Prior to joining Meridian Asset Management, Mr. Pirie was employed by Black Phoenix Consulting, LLC a firm specializes in forensic finance and accounting services including due diligence, loss of profit calculations, business valuations, and investigations with a focus on technical and statistical analyses. While employed there, Mr. Pirie was responsible for the due diligence study for 4 governmental entities measuring variable profit for the cities’ utility systems while modeling water consumption rates, wastewater rates, weather, and water conservation trends.
His other areas of experience include various oil and gas engagements which include the analysis of financial statements to evaluate historical operating patterns, business capital requirements, prospective industry/business growth, and to forecast potential operating levels.
Mr. Pirie graduated University of Miami, Magna Cum Laude with a Bachelor’s Degree in Finance.






















